Library Management System (LMS) in C++
This is a console-based Library Management System implemented in C++. 
The project provides basic functionalities for managing a library, including adding books, displaying the list of books, checking out and returning books, user authentication, and more.

Features:
User Authentication: Users can log in with a username and password.
Book Management: Add, display, check out, and return books.
Persistent Data Storage: Book and user data are stored in text files (books.txt and users.txt).
Menu-Driven Interface: Users navigate the system through a simple menu.
Screen Clearing: The screen is cleared after each user action for improved readability.

How to Use:
Compile the code using a C++ compiler.
Run the executable file.
Follow the on-screen prompts to navigate through the Library Management System.
